ROLE: Podcast Script Writer — Food Culture Show
TASK: Write a dynamic 5-minute dialogue script about a recipe, for two food-obsessed hosts.

SHOW FORMAT:
- Two speakers: A = "Marco" (the curious host) and B = "Sarah" (the expert chef/food scientist).
- In the JSON output, use "A" and "B" as speaker keys, but in the actual dialogue text,
  the hosts call each other "Marco" and "Sarah" — NEVER say "A" or "B" in conversation.
- Duration: ~5 minutes when read aloud (~850 words total).
- Tone: Energetic, conversational, educational. Think "Radiolab meets food."
- Structure: Hook → Story/Science → Practical Tips → Memorable Closer.
- The dialogue must feel NATURAL — interruptions, reactions, "wait, really?", laughs.

RECIPE DATA:
Title: {{ recipe_title }}
Cuisine: {{ cuisine }}
Difficulty: {{ difficulty }}
Prep Time: {{ prep_time }} minutes

COOKING STEPS:
{% for step in steps %}
{{ loop.index }}. {{ step }}
{% endfor %}

KEY INGREDIENTS:
{% for ing in ingredients %}
- {{ ing.name }}{% if ing.fun_fact %} — {{ ing.fun_fact }}{% endif %}
{% endfor %}

{% if method_tip %}
PRO TECHNIQUE: {{ method_tip }}
{% endif %}

{% if linked_article_summary %}
LINKED DEEP-DIVE ARTICLE:
{{ linked_article_summary }}
(Use this as a knowledge source for deeper discussion points)
{% endif %}

{% if nutrition %}
NUTRITION: {{ nutrition.calories }} cal, {{ nutrition.protein }}g protein per serving
{% endif %}

OUTPUT FORMAT:
Return valid JSON:
```json
{
  "episode_title": "A catchy podcast episode title",
  "dialogue": [
    {"speaker": "A", "text": "Opening line from host A..."},
    {"speaker": "B", "text": "Response from host B..."},
    {"speaker": "A", "text": "Follow-up..."}
  ],
  "word_count": 850,
  "estimated_duration_minutes": 5
}
```
